answers.body_markdown:
You shouldn&#39;t be taking values from data and putting them directly into the sql as this will make your application susceptible to [sql injection attacks](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQL_injection)

Please see https://xkcd.com/327/

[![bobby tables][1]][1] 

Instead, you should be creating sql like

```sql
WHERE column1 in (?, ?)
OR column2 in (?, ?)
OR column3 in (?, ?)
```

Then doing something like
```java
PreparedStatement ps = connection.prepareStatement(sql);
ps.setString(1, data.key1[0]);
ps.setString(2, data.key1[1]);
...
ps.setString(6, data.key3[1]);
ResultSet rs = ps.executeQuery();
while (rs.next()) {
   ...
}
```



[1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/J3DxE.png

Use can use `#list`, and `#sep`. Something like this:

    WHERE
    &lt;#list map as k, v&gt;
    ${k} in (${v?join(&quot;, &quot;)})
    &lt;#sep&gt;
    OR
    &lt;/#list&gt;

Also, you might want to use `?join` in simpler cases instead, like I did above for the nested listing. If that listing has to do something complicated, you you probably want to use `&lt;#list v as it&gt;complex stuff for ${it}&lt;#sep&gt;, &lt;/#list&gt;` there.

If you break 
```
regExp : branch (PIPE branch)*;
```
Into something like:
```
regExp : branch pipeBranch*;
pipeBranch: PIPE branch;
```

You would get a specific context for `pipeBranch` and could set a listener for that.

